{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| TUEVAL | Evaluator | Char | (EVAL) | Record Qualifier | Role of the person who provided the evaluation. Examples: "ADJUDICATION COMMITTEE", "(INDEPENDENT ASSESSOR)". This column can be left null when the investigator provides the complete set of data in the domain. However, the column should contain no null values when data from 1 or more independent assessors is included. For example, the rows attributed to the investigator can be left null, but all rows from an independent assessor must be populated. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| TUEVALID | Evaluator Identifier | Char | (MEDEVAL) | Variable Qualifier | Used to distinguish multiple evaluators with the same role recorded in ~EVAL. Examples: "RADIOLOGIST1", "RADIOLOGIST2". See assumption 9. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| TUACPTFL | Accepted Record Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | In cases where more than 1 independent assessor (e.g., "RADIOLOGIST 1", "RADIOLOGIST 2", "ADJUDICATION COMMITTEE") provide independent assessments at the same time point, this flag identifies the record that is considered to be the accepted assessment. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISITNUM | Visit Number | Num | | Timing | Identifies the record that is considered to be the accepted assessment. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISIT | Visit Name | Char | | Timing | Clinical encounter number. Numeric version of VISIT, used for sorting. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| VISITDY | Planned Study Day of the Visit | Num | | Timing | Protocol-defined description of a clinical encounter. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| TAETORD | Planned Order of Element within Arm | Num | | Timing | Number that gives the planned order of the element within the arm for the element in which the assessment was made. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| EPOCH | Epoch | Char | (EPOCH) | Timing | Epoch associated with the date/time at which the assessment was made. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| TUDTC | Date/Time of Tumor/Lesion Identification | Char | (ISO 8601 datetime or interval) | Timing | TUDTC variable represents the date of the scan/image/physical exam. TUDTC does not represent the date that the image was read to identify tumors. TUDTC also does not represent the VISIT date. | Exp |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Specification", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| TUDY | Study day of the Tumor/Lesion Identification | Num | | Timing | Study day of the scan/image/physical exam, measured as integer days. Algorithm for calculations must be relative to the sponsor-defined RFSTDTC variable in Demographics. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.12.1 Tumor/Lesion Identification (TU)", "atom_type": "HEADING", "verbatim": "TU – Assumptions", "heading_level": 5, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The TU domain should contain only 1 record for each unique tumor/lesion/location of interest identified by an assessor (e.g., investigator, independent assessor) per medical evaluator. The initial identification of a tumor/lesion/location of interest is done once, usually at baseline (e.g., identification of target and non-target tumors/lesions) of first appearance of new tumor/lesion. The identification information, including the location description, must not be repeated for every visit. A record is required in TU to identify and create the TULNKID where there are associated records in TR with matching TRLNKID. The following are examples of when post-baseline records might be included in the TU domain:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 1, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. A new tumor/lesion may emerge at any time during a study; therefore, a new post-baseline record would represent the identification of the new tumor/lesion.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 2, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0346_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 346, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. If a tumor/lesion identified at baseline subsequently splits into separate distinct tumors/lesions, then additional post-baseline records can be included to distinctly identify the split tumors/lesions.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 3, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. In situations where a re-baseline of targets and non-targets is required (e.g., a cross-over study), then a separate set of target and non-target tumors/lesions might be identified and those identification records would be represented.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 4, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. TRLNKID is used to relate an identification record in the TU domain to assessment records in the Tumor/Lesion Results (TR) domain. The organization of data across the TU and TR domains requires a linking mechanism. The TULNKID variable is used to provide a unique code for each identified tumor/lesion. The values of TULNKID are compound values that may carry the following information: an indication of the role (or assessor) providing the data record, when it is someone other than the principal investigator; an indication of whether the data record is for a target or non-target tumor/lesion; a tracking identifier or number; and an indication of whether the tumor/lesion has split (see assumption 3 for details on splitting). A RELREC relationship record can be created to describe the link, probably as a dataset-to-dataset link.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": 5, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "TUTESTCD/TUTEST values for this domain are published as Controlled Terminology. For some TUTESTCD/TUTEST values, CDISC CT includes codelists for use with TULORRES.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "CROSS_REF", "verbatim": "The associations between the test values and results are in the Oncology codeetable, which, along with the CT Rules for Oncology, is available at https://www.cdisc.org/standards/terminology/controlled-terminology.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["https://www.cdisc.org/standards/terminology/controlled-terminology"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "During the course of a trial, at a given visit, a tumor/lesion might split into one or more distinct tumors/lesions, or 2 or more tumors/lesions might merge to form a single tumor/lesion.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The following example shows the preferred approach for representing split lesions in TU.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "However, the approach depends on how the data for split and merged tumors/lesions are captured.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The preferred approach requires the measurements of each distinct tumor/lesion to be captured individually.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Example target tumor T04, identified at the screening visit, splits into 2 at week 16.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Two new records are created with TUTEST = \"Tumor Split\"; TULNKID reflects the split by adding 0.1 and 0.2 to the original TULNKID value.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
