{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a030", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| L04 | TUMIDENT | Tumor Identification | LOCATION OF INTEREST | BODY | PET SCAN |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0347_a031", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 347, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "4. During the course of a trial, when a new tumor/lesion is identified, a record must be included in both the TU and TR domains. At a minimum, the TR record would contain TRLNKID = \"NEW0\" and TRTESTCD = \"TUMSTATE\" and TRORRES = \"PRESENT\" for unequivocal new tumors.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0348_a001", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 348, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The TU record may contain different levels of detail depending upon the data collection methods employed.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0348_a002", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 348, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Although it is possible that a sponsor may have a different chosen method, the following are the most common scenarios:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0348_a003", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 348, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "a. The occurrence of a new tumor/lesion is the sole piece of information that a sponsor collects, because this is a sign of disease progression; no further details are required. In such cases, a record would be created where TUTEST = \"Tumor Identification\" and TUORRES = \"NEW\", and the identifier, TULNKID, would be populated in order to link to the associated information in the TR domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0348_a004", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 348, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "b. The occurrence of a new tumor/lesion and the anatomical location of that newly identified tumor/lesion are the only collected pieces of information. In this case, it is expected that a record would be created where TUTEST = \"Tumor Identification\" and TUORRES = \"NEW\"; the TULOC variable would be populated with the anatomical location information (the additional location variables may be populated depending on the level of detail collected), and the identifier, TULNKID, would be populated in order to link to the associated information in the TR domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0348_a005", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 348, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "c. The sponsor records the occurrence of a new tumor/lesion to the same level of detail as target tumors/lesions. For example, with the occurrence of a new tumor/lesion, its anatomical location and its measurement might be recorded. In this case, it is expected that a record would be created where TUTEST = \"Tumor Identification\" and TUORRES = \"NEW\". The TULOC variable would be populated with the anatomical location information (the additional location variables may be populated depending on the level of detail collected) and the identifier, TULNKID, would be populated in order to link to the associated information in the TR domain. In this scenario, measurements/assessments would also be recorded in the TR domain.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0348_a006", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 348, "page_region": "top", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "5. The additional anatomical location variables --LAT, --DIR, --PORTOT were added from the SDTM. These extra variables allow for more detailed information to be collected that further clarifies the value of the TULOC variable.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0348_a007", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 348, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "6. In the oncology setting, when a new tumor is identified, a record must be included in both the TU and TR domains. At a minimum, the TR record would contain TRLNKID = \"NEW0\" and TRTESTCD = \"TUMSTATE\" and TRORRES = \"PRESENT\" for unequivocal new tumors.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0348_a008", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 348, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "7. The acceptance flag variable (TUACPTFL) identifies records that have been determined to be the accepted assessment measurements by an independent assessor. This flag would be populated by an independent assessor and when multiple evaluations (e.g., \"RADIOLOGIST 1\", \"RADIOLOGIST 2\", \"ADJUDICATION COMMITTEE\") provide independent assessments at the same time point or an overall evaluation. This flag should not be used by a sponsor for any other purpose. It is not expected that the TUACPTFL flag would be populated by the sponsor; instead, that type of record selection should be handled in the analysis dataset (ADaM).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0348_a009", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 348, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "8. The evaluator-specified variable TUEVALID is used in conjunction with TUEVAL to provide additional detail regarding who is providing tumor identification information (e.g., TUEVAL = \"INDEPENDENT ASSESSOR\", TUEVALID = \"RADIOLOGIST 1\"). The TUEVALID variable is subject to controlled terminology. Note: TUEVAL must also be populated when TUEVALID is populated.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0348_a010", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 348, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "9. If indicator questions for specific types of tumor or lesions are collected (e.g., Does the subject have target tumors? Does the subject have any non-targets? Did the subject have metastatic disease at screening?), then these TUTEST will be included in TU. If indicator questions are not collected, do not introduce them into TU.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0348_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 348, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "TU – Assumptions", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example shows indicator TUTESTS for a subject with non-target lesions only.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.4", "ts": "2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
